output.title: How to come up with the best Robot ideas
output.description:
Have you ever wondered how great robots are designed? Does is seem like certain teams always come up with great ideas? The trick here is simple Practice and Experience. Engineering is not about knowing everything there is to know that is not possible. Engineering is about learning about different designs, building techniques, tools, etc and storing that knowledge in the back of your mind. When you are tasked with a challenge, you access that information and apply it to help come up with the best solution possible. 

Remember, designing a robot is only possible by accessing that information that you already know. In our limited time crunch we have limited time to research. For this reason it is important to spend the next few days looking at examples of robots, building techniques, and components and store that information in the back of your mind for build day. We are only as good as what we already know.

In these next few snowy days, I would like you to spend some time looking at the AndyMark website and seeing what they have. Read the manuals for different pieces that interest you. Is there a gear housing that looks really cool? Find out how it works! That new speed controller, that looks like it could be something we could use, how could we do that? Ask questions, take notes of items that interest you. The more you bring to the table on the design days, the better the solutions will be that you will come up with. The Chief Delphi Site has forums where people (endlessly) talk about all of this stuff. Use these resources, and have fun! This season is going to be exciting and quite possibly the best yet, but weve got a lot of work ahead of us. Be ready to bring you A game. See you all soon.
